recent_commits.message:
The class_labels should be ground truth data

Based on pytorch docs, the parameter "labels" of add_pr_curve() should be
ground truth data. But in Line 141, class_labels append our own
predictions. Therefore, I substitute "labels" for "predicted".

recent_commits.author: PowerBagel911
recent_commits.message:
Add enhanced and improved spam detection pipelines

Introduced enhanced_model_pipeline.py for a rich-feature spam detection pipeline and updated improved_model_pipeline.py for focused feature selection and model saving. Added new result CSVs, model artifacts, and visualizations. Updated .gitignore for new result files and removed/moved overfitting_analysis.png. Saved all trained models and preprocessors in timestamped folders with metadata and loading instructions.

recent_commits.author: PowerBagel911
recent_commits.message:
Remove model comparison pipeline and update visualizations

Deleted the comprehensive model comparison pipeline script, related result CSVs, and moved visualization output files into a dedicated 'visualization' directory. Updated 'simple_visualization_pipeline.py' to save figures in the new directory. This streamlines the repository by removing legacy model comparison artifacts and organizing visualization outputs.

recent_commits.author: PowerBagel911
recent_commits.message:
Tune model hyperparameters and update results

Adjusted hyperparameters for Random Forest and LSTM models in improved_model_pipeline.py to improve performance and regularization. Updated .gitignore to exclude new results files and .DS_Store. Added new results CSV, updated model and visualization outputs, and changed the default results file in simple_visualization_pipeline.py.

recent_commits.author: PowerBagel911
recent_commits.message:
Add overfitting-resistant spam detection pipeline

Introduces improved_model_pipeline.py with overfitting prevention techniques, including feature selection, SMOTE, regularization, and stratified validation. Adds model results CSVs, LSTM model file, and new visualizations for dataset analysis, model comparison, and training progress. Updates requirements.txt to include imbalanced-learn. Also adds a simple visualization pipeline using matplotlib and seaborn.
